==Demographics==
In 2010, it had a population of 59.<ref name="Census 2010">{{Cite web| url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US5373065| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Twin Lakes CDP, Washington| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=October 24, 2016}}{{dead link|bot=medic|date=April 2020}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> The census reported that 36 of the inhabitants were male, and 23 were female.<ref name="City-Data.com">{{cite web | url=http://www.city-data.com/city/Twin-Lakes-Washington.html | title=Twin Lakes, Washington | accessdate=19 August 2014}}</ref>

